metadata.description:
i wrote ‘Default’ after a conversation with a friend where i realized i had been changing myself for someone i thought i loved. ‘Default’ is about fighting the feeling of shape shifting for someone else - but also how addicting it is trying to be everything to everyone. 

‘Default’ is the last single before my second EP releases in november. the golden egg winner will receive a 1/1 piece of merch and tickets to one of my upcoming headlining shows.

written by ben kessler, sean cook, karissa bone
produced by sean cook
artwork by josefine cardoni

lyrics.text:
There’s static on my tv
I feel it feels the friction from the couch
It’s like your thoughts are in my bloodstream
Deleting words before they even leave my mouth
There’s things I’d never tell you
I hate the way that you pick up the phone
And all your fears you never worked through
It must mean something that I’m different alone

There’s versions of me fighting layers of you
Let you pick at the seams I’d rewrite myself for you

Factory reset
If I change all of my default settings
Would I be someone you need then?
Want you to want me when I’m not pretending
Forget all your feelings
If I let you see straight through my skin
